4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the representation of phrase trees using matrices and triangles, which are common data structures in computer science. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely sub-category, but it is possible as the paper deals with the analysis of linguistic structures, which can be related to speech and sound processing.
